charmed_rust-dnt: [PropTest] Property-based testing for input parsing

## Objective
Integrate property-based tests into the CI pipeline with proper configuration for test case counts, failure persistence, regression testing, and performance optimization.

## Detailed Requirements

### 1. Proptest Configuration File

Create `proptest.toml` at the workspace root:

```toml
# Proptest configuration for charmed_rust
# https://altsysrq.github.io/proptest-book/proptest/config.html

# Default profile (local development)
[profile.default]
cases = 256
max_shrink_iters = 1000
source_file = "target/proptest-regressions"
fork = false

# CI profile (thorough testing)
[profile.ci]
cases = 1000
max_shrink_iters = 10000
source_file = "target/proptest-regressions"
fork = false
timeout = 60000  # 60 seconds per test

# Fast profile (quick smoke test)
[profile.smoke]
cases = 50
max_shrink_iters = 100
source_file = "target/proptest-regressions"

# Nightly profile (extensive fuzzing)
[profile.nightly]
cases = 10000
max_shrink_iters = 100000
source_file = "target/proptest-regressions"
timeout = 300000  # 5 minutes per test
```

### 2. CI Workflow Configuration

Add to `.github/workflows/ci.yml`:

```yaml
name: CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [main, master]
  pull_request:
    branches: [main, master]
  schedule:
    # Nightly runs at 2 AM UTC
    - cron: '0 2 * * *'

env:
  CARGO_TERM_COLOR: always
  RUST_BACKTRACE: 1

jobs:
  property-tests:
    name: Property Tests
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install Rust
        uses: dtolnay/rust-action@stable
        with:
          components: rustfmt, clippy

      - name: Cache cargo registry
        uses: actions/cache@v4
        with:
          path: |
            ~/.cargo/registry
            ~/.cargo/git
            target
          key: ${{ runner.os }}-cargo-proptest-${{ hashFiles('**/Cargo.lock') }}

      - name: Cache proptest regressions
        uses: actions/cache@v4
        with:
          path: target/proptest-regressions
          key: proptest-regressions-${{ github.sha }}
          restore-keys: |
            proptest-regressions-

      - name: Run property tests (CI profile)
        run: |
          PROPTEST_CASES=1000 cargo test --features proptest -- --test-threads=1 proptest
        env:
          RUST_LOG: proptest=info

      - name: Upload regression files
        if: failure()
        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: proptest-regressions
          path: target/proptest-regressions/

  property-tests-nightly:
    name: Property Tests (Nightly)
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    if: github.event_name == 'schedule'
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install Rust
        uses: dtolnay/rust-action@stable

      - name: Run extensive property tests
        run: |
          PROPTEST_CASES=10000 cargo test --features proptest -- --test-threads=1 proptest
        env:
          RUST_LOG: proptest=debug
        timeout-minutes: 30

      - name: Upload regression files
        if: failure()
        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: proptest-regressions-nightly
          path: target/proptest-regressions/
```

### 3. Feature Flag Configuration

Update `Cargo.toml` for each crate with proptest:

```toml
[features]
default = []
proptest = ["dep:proptest", "dep:proptest-derive"]

[dev-dependencies]
proptest = { version = "1.4", optional = true }
proptest-derive = { version = "0.4", optional = true }
test-log = { version = "0.2", features = ["trace"] }
tracing-subscriber = { version = "0.3", features = ["env-filter"] }
```

### 4. Test Organization

Structure property tests for CI:

```rust
// crates/bubbletea/src/lib.rs
#[cfg(all(test, feature = "proptest"))]
mod proptest_tests;

// crates/bubbletea/src/proptest_tests/mod.rs
mod generators;
mod key_tests;
mod mouse_tests;
mod roundtrip_tests;

use proptest::prelude::*;

/// Configure proptest based on environment
fn proptest_config() -> ProptestConfig {
    let cases = std::env::var("PROPTEST_CASES")
        .ok()
        .and_then(|s| s.parse().ok())
        .unwrap_or(256);

    let max_shrink = std::env::var("PROPTEST_MAX_SHRINK")
        .ok()
        .and_then(|s| s.parse().ok())
        .unwrap_or(1000);

    ProptestConfig {
        cases,
        max_shrink_iters: max_shrink,
        source_file: Some("target/proptest-regressions"),
        ..ProptestConfig::default()
    }
}
```

### 5. Regression Test Persistence

Ensure regression files are tracked:

```gitignore
# .gitignore - DO NOT ignore regression files
# target/proptest-regressions/  # Keep these tracked!
```

Create a script to manage regressions:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
# scripts/proptest-regressions.sh

case "$1" in
  list)
    find target/proptest-regressions -name "*.txt" 2>/dev/null
    ;;
  clean)
    rm -rf target/proptest-regressions
    echo "Cleaned proptest regressions"
    ;;
  commit)
    git add target/proptest-regressions/
    git commit -m "chore: update proptest regression files"
    ;;
  *)
    echo "Usage: $0 {list|clean|commit}"
    exit 1
    ;;
esac
```

### 6. Performance Optimization for CI

```rust
// Optimize test execution in CI
proptest! {
    #![proptest_config(ProptestConfig {
        // Fewer cases in CI to balance coverage vs time
        cases: if std::env::var("CI").is_ok() { 1000 } else { 256 },
        // Longer shrinking in CI for better failure reports
        max_shrink_iters: if std::env::var("CI").is_ok() { 10000 } else { 1000 },
        // Fail fast in CI
        max_global_rejects: 10000,
        ..ProptestConfig::default()
    })]

    #[test]
    fn expensive_property_test(input in arb_complex_input()) {
        // Test body
    }
}
```

